🔹 🎯 Task 1: Shift Array Left
You are writing a utility that rotates all elements of an array one position to the left (the first element wraps to the end).
📥 Input:
int[] arr;
⚙️ Requirements:
•
Write a method shiftLeft(int[] arr) that modifies the array in place
•
The first element moves to the last position; every other element shifts one index to the left
•
Print the resulting array on one line, space-separated
⚠️ Watch out:
•
In JS, arrays are objects — but Java arrays are also reference types, so shiftLeft receives the reference and mutations inside the method affect the original. However, reassigning the parameter (arr = new int[]{...}) inside the method does not affect the caller's variable. Mutate the contents, not the reference.
•
Save arr[0] before the loop or you'll overwrite it.
📤 Output format:
Shifted: X X X X
📌 Test cases:
Input: arr = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
Output: Shifted: 2 3 4 5 1

Input: arr = {42}
Output: Shifted: 42

Input: arr = {7, 3}
Output: Shifted: 3 7

Input: arr = {-1, 0, 1}
Output: Shifted: 0 1 -1

