🔹 🎯 Task 2: Column Sum of a 2D Array
You are building a report tool that sums each column of a rectangular 2D grid and prints the totals.
📥 Input:
int[][] grid;   // rectangular — all rows same length
⚙️ Requirements:
•
Write a method columnSums(int[][] grid) that returns a new int[] where each element is the sum of the corresponding column
•
Print each column sum on its own line as "Col X: Y"
⚠️ Watch out:
•
In JS you'd use arr[0].length instinctively. In Java, grid.length is the number of rows; grid[0].length is the number of columns — easy to swap and get an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException instead of a compile error.
•
Java 2D arrays are arrays-of-arrays, not a true matrix. Each row is an independent int[].
📤 Output format:
Col 0: X
Col 1: X
...
📌 Test cases:
Input:
grid = {
  {1, 2, 3},
  {4, 5, 6},
  {7, 8, 9}
}
Output:
Col 0: 12
Col 1: 15
Col 2: 18

Input:
grid = {
  {10, -10},
  {5,    5}
}
Output:
Col 0: 15
Col 1: -5

Input:
grid = {
  {0, 0, 0}
}
Output:
Col 0: 0
Col 1: 0
Col 2: 0

Input:
grid = {
  {-3, 4},
  {-1, 2},
  { 2,-6}
}
Output:
Col 0: -2
Col 1: 0

